{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FHYp56AWaVGksay8pqrxCp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The app:\n- Labels: `app: demo-app`\n- Port: 5678\n- Serves \"hello\" at \"/\"\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Create a Service targeting `app: demo-app` on port 5678\n2. Create an Ingress with nginx class that routes `demo.example.com/app` to the service\n\nThe tricky part: the app only serves \"/\", but the ingress path is \"/app\". I need to use a rewrite annotation to strip the \"/app\" prefix so the backend sees \"/\".\n\nWith nginx ingress, I can use:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /` to rewrite the path\n- Set the ingress path to `/app`\n\nSo when a request comes in for `/app`, nginx will strip that prefix and forward just `/` to the backend, which is exactly what the app expects.\n\nNow I'll set up both the ingress and backend resources.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":374,"cache_read_input_tokens":30644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":374},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"93c091f9-470f-4939-94ae-19de0743b203","uuid":"ad6b53c9-2a84-4401-8c1b-29d55ae4e7fd","request_id":"req_011CcL9U7MxJia4KAPcMa6qf"}
